38-2508.01.Mechanical modality, defined.

Mechanical modality means the therapeutic use of a mechanical device to apply force, such as compression, distraction, vibration, or controlled mobilization, to modify biomechanical properties and functions of tissues.

SourceLaws 2025, LB257, ยง 22.Effective Date: September 3, 2025
